WEBVTT

00:09.052 --> 00:10.097
Previously onWhy Women Kill...

00:10.140 --> 00:12.621
I have a date.With your married man.

00:12.664 --> 00:13.622
It's at this
really fancy nightclub.

00:13.665 --> 00:15.711
He's taking you out.

00:15.754 --> 00:17.887
In public.

00:17.930 --> 00:19.889
I thought Rob was taking her
to the club tonight.

00:19.932 --> 00:22.761
Do you honestly think
I'm going to let that happen?

00:22.805 --> 00:23.980
Listen, when you were
in my office earlier,

00:24.024 --> 00:25.808
did you happen to move
any papers?

00:25.851 --> 00:27.940
I know better
than to touch your things.

00:27.984 --> 00:29.507
I'll have to stay late
and redo it.

00:31.683 --> 00:33.381
APRIL:
Would you like to come with me
to the club tonight?

00:33.424 --> 00:34.382
Rob canceled on me.

00:34.425 --> 00:35.687
I love music.

00:35.731 --> 00:37.994
I used to play the piano.Do you still play?

00:38.038 --> 00:40.736
My husband...
didn't care for my playing.

00:40.779 --> 00:43.043
Oh, honey.
Your husband's dead.

00:43.086 --> 00:45.654
Don't you think it's time
you stopped listening to him?

00:48.048 --> 00:49.484
Honey!

00:49.527 --> 00:51.312
TOMMY: Maybe when Mr. Grove moves out,

00:51.355 --> 00:52.313
we could start doing this
in your bed.

00:52.356 --> 00:53.662
He won't be leaving

00:53.705 --> 00:55.316
until after
my daughter's wedding.

00:55.359 --> 00:57.318
Well, it--
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:57.361 --> 00:58.623
That's two months away.

00:58.667 --> 01:00.625
She gave me her hand
in marriage.

01:00.669 --> 01:02.627
SIMONE: Karl...KARL: And I'm
never going

01:02.671 --> 01:04.716
to let it go.
Oh!

01:04.760 --> 01:05.848
KARL:
Bloody hell!

01:05.891 --> 01:07.110
I got fired.

01:07.154 --> 01:08.372
I'm not surprised.

01:08.416 --> 01:09.678
Simone...
One day,

01:09.721 --> 01:10.679
I will divorce Karl,

01:10.722 --> 01:11.984
but I will never hate him.

01:12.028 --> 01:13.116
Where does that leave me?

01:13.160 --> 01:14.726
In the back of a van,

01:14.770 --> 01:16.119
having a marvelous time.

01:16.163 --> 01:17.642
Van came with the job, so...

01:17.686 --> 01:19.122
We'll figure it out.

01:19.166 --> 01:20.993
I'm not worried
about Duke anymore.

01:21.037 --> 01:22.691
He stopped texting me.

01:22.734 --> 01:23.953
ELI: So what's
his deal?

01:23.996 --> 01:25.302
Is he crazy?
A little.

01:25.346 --> 01:26.912
He was always accusing me
of cheating on him.

01:26.956 --> 01:28.653
Come with us
to Venice tomorrow.

01:28.697 --> 01:31.439
Oh, my God!Tomorrow? Really?

01:31.482 --> 01:33.876
Are you going to Venice?I don't know yet.

01:33.919 --> 01:35.356
ELI:
I asked you,

01:35.399 --> 01:36.661
before, if you were
in love with her.

01:36.705 --> 01:39.360
Jade is the only thing
in my life that is easy.

01:39.403 --> 01:40.404
Live with us.

01:40.448 --> 01:42.014
Be with us.

01:42.058 --> 01:43.581
You just got home.

01:53.548 --> 01:56.551
♪ L is for the way you look

01:56.594 --> 01:59.380
♪ At me

01:59.423 --> 02:03.732
♪ O is for the only one

02:03.775 --> 02:06.735
♪ I see

02:06.778 --> 02:09.041
♪ V is very, very

02:09.085 --> 02:11.696
♪ Extraordinary

02:11.740 --> 02:15.787
♪ E is even more than anyone

02:15.831 --> 02:18.181
♪ That you adore can

02:18.225 --> 02:20.662
♪ Love is all

02:20.705 --> 02:24.405
♪ That I can give to you

02:24.448 --> 02:26.146
♪ Love is more

02:26.189 --> 02:30.498
♪ Than just a game for two

02:30.541 --> 02:33.631
♪ Two in love can make it

02:33.675 --> 02:36.765
♪ Take my heart
and please don't break it ♪

02:36.808 --> 02:39.420
♪ Love was made

02:39.463 --> 02:42.553
♪ For me and you...

02:57.960 --> 03:02.094
The purpose of an autopsy
is to provide clarity.

03:02.138 --> 03:04.967
How did the victim die?

03:05.010 --> 03:08.797
Was death the result
of a gunshot?

03:10.190 --> 03:11.669
Stabbing?

03:14.150 --> 03:15.978
Poison?

03:16.021 --> 03:19.590
How someone is killed
is easy to understand.

03:19.634 --> 03:23.855
Why it happened,
that's never so simple.

03:23.899 --> 03:28.730
But it always begins
with a choice.

03:28.773 --> 03:31.080
It might be a decision

03:31.123 --> 03:34.736
to conduct a tawdry affair.

03:34.779 --> 03:38.522
A plan to keep secrets
from a loved one.

03:39.958 --> 03:42.178
Or an agreement

03:42.222 --> 03:46.748
to bring a stranger
into your bed.

03:46.791 --> 03:51.622
Yes. People make all sorts
of questionable choices.

03:51.666 --> 03:56.061
Of course, that's what
keeps me in business.

04:04.244 --> 04:06.768
Our waitress
is giving me odd looks.

04:06.811 --> 04:09.161
You're wearing sunglasses
indoors, at night.

04:09.205 --> 04:12.077
I think she recognizes me.I don't even
recognize you

04:12.121 --> 04:14.254
and we've had sex ten times.

04:14.297 --> 04:15.516
Lower your voice.Relax.

04:15.559 --> 04:17.909
Nobody here recognizes you.

04:19.084 --> 04:20.782
Let me see your eyes.

04:24.568 --> 04:27.789
So, I got you a present.

04:27.832 --> 04:30.531
Jewelry?

04:30.574 --> 04:32.576
You shouldn't have.

04:37.625 --> 04:38.887
It's called a Swatch.

04:38.930 --> 04:40.628
And...

04:40.671 --> 04:42.238
it's waterproof.

04:42.282 --> 04:45.197
Oh, so it's safe
from my tears of joy.

04:46.373 --> 04:48.549
I wanted
to do something special.

04:48.592 --> 04:49.898
It's our first date.

04:49.941 --> 04:52.553
I mean, outside of the van.

04:52.596 --> 04:54.990
I'm not sure I'd call it a date.

04:55.033 --> 04:58.123
Why not? We're at a table,
and there's food.

05:00.648 --> 05:03.041
I wouldn't call it food, either.

05:03.085 --> 05:04.913
You don't make it very easy
to be your boyfriend.

05:04.956 --> 05:06.349
Boyfriend?

05:06.393 --> 05:08.612
Ah, another word
you don't like.

05:08.656 --> 05:11.746
It's just not
how I would describe you.

05:11.789 --> 05:13.748
What would you call me, then?

05:13.791 --> 05:17.099
Your lover?
Why do you need

05:17.142 --> 05:18.361
a job title?

05:18.405 --> 05:20.755
What's wrong with "Tommy"?

05:21.973 --> 05:24.933
Are you gonna put it on?

05:24.976 --> 05:27.109
Why would I do that?

05:27.152 --> 05:29.894
Because it's a gift,
and I'm asking you to.

05:29.938 --> 05:31.635
Oh, for God's sake.

05:31.679 --> 05:33.376
What's wrong?

05:33.420 --> 05:35.247
Am-am I embarrassing you?

05:35.291 --> 05:37.032
Shh. Shush. Sit down.

05:37.075 --> 05:38.860
Oh, I'm sorry.
Next time, I'll buy you a gift

05:38.903 --> 05:40.775
that you'll actually wear
on a date with me,

05:40.818 --> 05:42.733
like a ski mask.

05:42.777 --> 05:44.126
Tommy.

05:44.169 --> 05:46.302
Uh, what did I do now?

05:50.915 --> 05:52.308
Can I get you anything else
to eat?

05:52.352 --> 05:55.877
Oh, God, no.
The food is dreadful here.

05:55.920 --> 05:57.966
And he's too young for you,

05:58.009 --> 06:00.316
while we're offering
unsolicited opinions.

06:14.765 --> 06:16.985
Sheila. What can I do for you?

06:17.028 --> 06:18.639
I have no food in my house,

06:18.682 --> 06:21.076
and my kids are starting
to make some real ugly threats.

06:21.119 --> 06:22.991
Maybe I can find
a jar of peanut butter.

06:23.034 --> 06:25.385
That's more
than they deserve.

06:27.691 --> 06:29.301
What's with the skates?

06:29.345 --> 06:31.652
BETH ANN:
They're cute, huh?
Rob bought them for me

06:31.695 --> 06:32.914
on our first date.

06:32.957 --> 06:34.176
He took me to
Happytime Roller Rink.

06:34.219 --> 06:35.743
So why are you
digging them up now?

06:35.786 --> 06:38.746
I'm going skating
later today, with April.

06:38.789 --> 06:40.835
The waitress?Oh, yes.

06:40.878 --> 06:43.359
Last week, we went
to an Andy Warhol exhibit.

06:43.403 --> 06:45.187
Next week,
she's going to teach me to surf.

06:45.230 --> 06:48.973
Can you imagine? Me, surfing?

06:49.017 --> 06:50.845
I thought the plan was
to gain the girl's trust

06:50.888 --> 06:53.108
and convince her
to end the affair.

06:53.151 --> 06:54.762
That's what I'm doing.

06:54.805 --> 06:56.764
You sure?
'Cause it sounds like

06:56.807 --> 06:58.287
the two of you
are becoming close.

06:58.330 --> 07:00.463
Well, maybe a little.

07:00.507 --> 07:02.987
April is very sweet.

07:03.031 --> 07:04.989
She's so free-spirited.

07:05.033 --> 07:07.383
You wouldn't believe
the fun we have together.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.298
Mm-hmm. She sounds nice.

07:09.341 --> 07:11.692
For a girl who's sleeping
with your husband.

07:11.735 --> 07:13.433
I know it's odd, but I like her.

07:13.476 --> 07:15.347
I can't help it.

07:15.391 --> 07:17.698
What's wrong with her
being a friend?

07:17.741 --> 07:19.700
Nothing.

07:19.743 --> 07:22.746
As long as you don't forget
she's also the enemy.

07:28.099 --> 07:32.800
Okay. Well, how about, uh, you
know, classic "she's our lover"?

07:32.843 --> 07:34.932
Oof. That is
too sexual.

07:34.976 --> 07:38.806
Yeah? All right.
Um, our "special friend"?

07:38.849 --> 07:41.069
That makes me sound slow.

07:42.940 --> 07:47.075
All right. Uh, she's the third
prong of our throuple.

07:47.118 --> 07:49.207
Ugh. Barf.

07:49.251 --> 07:50.731
Well, now that Jade's
gonna live with us,

07:50.774 --> 07:51.993
we got to have some way
to introduce her.

07:54.256 --> 07:57.433
Well, why don't we just say
she's family?

07:57.477 --> 08:00.262
Aww. I love that.ELI:
Yeah.

08:00.305 --> 08:03.221
That's nice.

08:03.265 --> 08:05.397
TAYLOR:
Wait.

08:05.441 --> 08:07.399
Jade, does that look
like Duke's truck to you?

08:07.443 --> 08:10.054
Oh, shit.

08:10.098 --> 08:13.971
Wait, like, like, scary ex Duke?

08:14.015 --> 08:15.538
Did you tell him you
were staying here?

08:15.582 --> 08:18.236
No. I didn't tell anyone.

08:18.280 --> 08:20.238
Oh, God. He's getting
out the car.

08:20.282 --> 08:21.370
Oh, fuck, fuck, fuck,
fuck, fuck, fuck...Okay, it's okay, it's okay.

08:21.413 --> 08:22.458
Okay, all right, all right.

08:22.502 --> 08:24.155
Look, don't worry.
It's gonna be okay.

08:24.199 --> 08:26.288
I got this.Wait, what do you mean,
you got this?

08:26.331 --> 08:27.811
I'm gonna talk
to him. You know?

08:27.855 --> 08:28.943
Man to man.No. Eli...

08:28.986 --> 08:30.161
No-- don't-- E...

08:30.205 --> 08:32.990
Oh, that's not good. Okay.

08:33.034 --> 08:34.949
Can I help you?

08:34.992 --> 08:36.341
Yeah, I'm looking
for my girlfriend.

08:36.385 --> 08:38.256
A guy told me
that she's staying here.

08:38.300 --> 08:40.476
Oh. Uh, who's your girlfriend?

08:40.520 --> 08:41.477
Jade.

08:41.521 --> 08:43.000
Jade.

08:43.044 --> 08:44.567
Jade, Jade, Jade, Jade,
Jade, Jade, Jade...

08:44.611 --> 08:45.916
No-- Jade who?

08:45.960 --> 08:47.265
She's in that window, man.

08:49.354 --> 08:51.792
Oh, Jade. Right. Yeah.Yeah.

08:51.835 --> 08:53.968
I need to talk to her.Oh, okay.
Well, uh, the thing is,

08:54.011 --> 08:55.883
she's not really
available right now, so...Yeah, I think she is.

08:55.926 --> 08:57.406
Yep.

08:57.449 --> 08:59.364
Oh, shit.

08:59.408 --> 09:00.975
All right, look-- look, man.

09:01.018 --> 09:02.498
I don't want to get physical
with you, okay?

09:02.542 --> 09:04.500
You're right. You don't.

09:05.849 --> 09:07.503
What do you think you're doing?

09:07.547 --> 09:09.897
You must be the fuck buddy.

09:09.940 --> 09:12.987
And you must be Duke,
the two-time felon.

09:13.030 --> 09:15.293
Those were both
felonies, right?

09:15.337 --> 09:17.861
So if I were to call
the cops and they came here

09:17.905 --> 09:20.037
to see you committing
a third assault,

09:20.081 --> 09:22.213
that sounds like
three strikes to me.

09:24.128 --> 09:27.958
This is the part where you walk
away to avoid going to prison.

09:29.612 --> 09:31.005
Tell Jade I'll be in touch.

09:38.055 --> 09:40.231
You know, that was unnecessary.

09:40.275 --> 09:42.146
I had it under control.

09:42.190 --> 09:44.932
Honey, it was a team effort.I know.

09:44.975 --> 09:46.629
Thank you so much.

09:46.673 --> 09:48.370
I was so freaked out.

09:48.413 --> 09:51.068
Aww.Oh...

09:51.112 --> 09:52.287
You're my hero.

09:52.330 --> 09:53.854
Jade, I'm not your hero.

09:53.897 --> 09:56.073
I just, I'm--
want to make sure you're okay.

10:03.951 --> 10:06.344
Ooh, we should invite
the Prescotts to the wedding.

10:06.388 --> 10:07.694
Must we?

10:07.737 --> 10:09.391
Well, I can't
stand them, either,

10:09.434 --> 10:11.654
but they spent $10,000
at the gallery last year.

10:11.698 --> 10:13.482
Just put them on the maybe list.

10:13.525 --> 10:15.789
Another maybe?
Amy will be here in an hour.

10:15.832 --> 10:18.356
We promised we'd have
the guest list done.

10:18.400 --> 10:21.011
What about the... Randalls?

10:21.055 --> 10:23.013
Absolutely not. I despise them.

10:23.057 --> 10:25.973
Since when? We went to their
son's wedding a month ago.

10:26.016 --> 10:28.453
And never got a thank you note
for the candy dish.

10:28.497 --> 10:30.542
That's awfully petty.I agree.

10:30.586 --> 10:32.414
How hard is it to
write a simple note?

10:32.457 --> 10:34.372
I meant you.

10:34.416 --> 10:35.678
What is going on?

10:35.722 --> 10:37.549
What do you mean, "going on"?

10:37.593 --> 10:41.118
You've been in a foul mood ever
since you came home last night.

10:41.162 --> 10:43.381
What could it be?

10:43.425 --> 10:46.950
Hmm. I broke a nail?
No, that's not it.

10:46.994 --> 10:49.126
My husband sleeps with men?
No, couldn't be that.

10:49.170 --> 10:51.389
Fine. Don't tell me.

10:51.433 --> 10:54.784
Look, we have prepaid
the caterer for 400 guests.

10:54.828 --> 10:56.568
If we don't
finish our list,

10:56.612 --> 10:59.876
then Brad's family will invite
more rubes from Oklahoma,

10:59.920 --> 11:02.400
and the entire wedding
will turn into a hoedown.

11:02.444 --> 11:05.055
Do they have hoedowns
in Oklahoma?

11:05.099 --> 11:06.578
Oh, well,
they do in the musical.

11:06.622 --> 11:07.928
First number of act two.

11:07.971 --> 11:11.409
How did I not know
what I was getting with you?

11:11.453 --> 11:12.715
What?

11:14.064 --> 11:16.023
Oh, Amy, you're early.

11:16.066 --> 11:18.547
We haven't quite finished
the guest list yet.

11:18.590 --> 11:21.071
Brad slept
with his ex-girlfriend.

11:21.115 --> 11:24.118
The wedding's off.
I require wine.

11:26.598 --> 11:30.428
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa... ♪

11:30.472 --> 11:32.430
Watch out, watch ou-- watch out!

11:32.474 --> 11:35.433
♪ Poetry in motion

11:39.481 --> 11:41.657
♪ A wave out on the ocean

11:41.701 --> 11:45.182
♪ Could never move that way...

11:45.226 --> 11:47.837
That was a blast.

11:47.881 --> 11:51.841
Can I just say, every
day I spend with you

11:51.885 --> 11:53.974
feels like an adventure.

11:54.017 --> 11:55.932
We do have fun together,
don't we?

11:55.976 --> 11:57.847
To be honest,

11:57.891 --> 12:00.241
I've been feeling
a little lonely in L.A.

12:01.503 --> 12:03.200
I know how you feel.

12:03.244 --> 12:07.639
It's nice to
have a real girlfriend out here.

12:09.685 --> 12:12.166
Well, it's getting late.
I should go.

12:12.209 --> 12:15.909
Wait, do you think you have time
for one more adventure tonight?

12:15.952 --> 12:17.780
I suppose.

12:17.824 --> 12:20.043
Okay.

12:20.087 --> 12:21.175
April?

12:21.218 --> 12:22.829
What are you up to?

12:27.529 --> 12:29.661
Go ahead. Try one.

12:29.705 --> 12:32.969
Brownies?
How are they an adventure?

12:33.013 --> 12:35.058
My recipe calls
for a special ingredient.

12:35.102 --> 12:37.800
Like what?
Grass.

12:37.844 --> 12:40.237
From your lawn?

12:40.281 --> 12:43.806
No,
I'm talking about pot.

12:43.850 --> 12:45.982
You know, marijuana?

12:46.026 --> 12:48.985
You mean reefer?

12:50.204 --> 12:51.988
Oh. Look, it's not a big deal.

12:52.032 --> 12:53.163
Lots of people do it.

12:53.207 --> 12:55.209
Criminals. Musicians.

12:55.252 --> 12:56.863
Please don't be angry.

12:56.906 --> 12:58.995
You are a good girl.
How could you do such a thing?

12:59.039 --> 13:01.041
Rob wanted to.

13:04.000 --> 13:05.828
Your married man?

13:05.872 --> 13:07.090
Yeah.

13:07.134 --> 13:10.528
That stuns me.

13:10.572 --> 13:12.879
Given how you've described him.

13:12.922 --> 13:14.532
He can be such a square.

13:14.576 --> 13:16.883
I think he was just looking
for a way to cut loose.

13:16.926 --> 13:18.841
Oh.

13:21.017 --> 13:22.584
Look, I really didn't mean
to offend you.

13:22.627 --> 13:26.806
I'm fine. It's just something
I wasn't expecting.

13:29.199 --> 13:30.592
So are we friends again?

13:32.333 --> 13:34.770
Great.
I'll go put these away.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.119
Wait.
Hmm?

13:42.865 --> 13:44.736
Oh, what the heck.

13:53.136 --> 13:55.008
But how did you find out?I've had my suspicions

13:55.051 --> 13:57.880
for a while, and then Brad
finally admitted

13:57.924 --> 13:59.577
that he's been lying
to me about Cindy

13:59.621 --> 14:01.057
the whole time
we've been engaged.

14:01.101 --> 14:02.885
I know so many whores
named Cindy.

14:02.929 --> 14:06.715
And did I mention she's fat?
140 pounds if she's an ounce.

14:06.758 --> 14:09.761
Oh, 140, where did he
find her, a carnival?

14:09.805 --> 14:11.763
You know, darling,
it's not even noon yet.

14:11.807 --> 14:13.983
My fiancé fucked a beluga whale.

14:14.027 --> 14:15.593
Can I please get
some support here?

14:15.637 --> 14:17.682
I'm sorry.

14:17.726 --> 14:21.121
Uh, so he's been sleeping
with Cindy this whole time?

14:21.164 --> 14:22.774
No, I didn't say that.

14:22.818 --> 14:24.776
I'm confused.

14:24.820 --> 14:26.996
He's been lying the whole time.

14:27.040 --> 14:29.085
They hooked up that weekend
you took me to Hawaii.

14:29.129 --> 14:30.870
Hang on, that was
two years ago.

14:30.913 --> 14:32.262
Were you and Brad
even engaged yet?

14:32.306 --> 14:34.612
No, but we were together.

14:34.656 --> 14:36.614
Mm, off and on.

14:36.658 --> 14:38.790
Okay, Brad hadn't
proposed yet,

14:38.834 --> 14:40.227
but we both knew
he was going to.

14:40.270 --> 14:41.619
Exactly.

14:41.663 --> 14:42.925
Yeah, or at least I knew.

14:42.969 --> 14:44.622
Well, maybe you
should've told him.

14:44.666 --> 14:46.102
I can't believe
you're taking Brad's side.

14:46.146 --> 14:47.625
I'm just saying

14:47.669 --> 14:50.019
the situation is not
quite so cut and dried.

14:50.063 --> 14:53.631
Brad is a good man.
You might consider forgiveness.

14:53.675 --> 14:55.982
Forgiveness?

14:56.025 --> 14:58.201
Boy, did you marry
