30:58.160 --> 31:00.815
Why are you on Brad's side?
What's changed?

31:00.859 --> 31:02.904
Who got to you?

31:02.948 --> 31:04.950
Hello.
Was it him?

31:04.993 --> 31:06.908
It was you.
This is all your fault.

31:06.952 --> 31:09.476
Yes, I'm sure it is. Sorry,
what are we talking about?

31:09.519 --> 31:13.306
Amy's decided to pay Brad back
by seducing Tommy Harte.

31:13.349 --> 31:16.265
Tommy? Isn't he a
little young for you?

31:16.309 --> 31:19.616
What is he, 17?He's 18 and mature for his age.

31:21.880 --> 31:23.490
But that's beside the point.

31:23.533 --> 31:24.926
You made a promise,
young lady,

31:24.970 --> 31:27.276
to Brad, to us,
and to the Biltmore Hotel.

31:27.320 --> 31:29.539
Oh, you're one
to talk about promises.

31:29.583 --> 31:32.151
You divorced Daddy,
the guy after him,

31:32.194 --> 31:33.848
and now with Karl sleeping

31:33.892 --> 31:36.024
in the guest room, I'm assuming
he's on his way out as well.

31:36.068 --> 31:38.505
Look.

31:38.548 --> 31:40.333
I love Brad,

31:40.376 --> 31:42.335
but I don't know
if I can trust him,

31:42.378 --> 31:44.119
and I don't want to be
another you.

31:45.294 --> 31:47.470
With three husbands by 40.

31:54.477 --> 31:56.871
Your keys are in the freezer.

31:56.915 --> 31:58.960
Go.

31:59.004 --> 32:02.181
A-Amy, Amy.
You're right.

32:02.224 --> 32:06.925
Your mother and I are sorting
through some issues,

32:06.968 --> 32:09.449
and I'm not
a perfect husband,

32:09.492 --> 32:11.146
and maybe Brad
won't be either,

32:11.190 --> 32:13.583
but love
is always a risk,

32:13.627 --> 32:16.891
and I know it's easy to think
this is never going to last,

32:16.935 --> 32:19.502
so why don't I
end it now, but...

32:19.546 --> 32:22.941
the chance for love doesn't
come around every day.

32:22.984 --> 32:24.246
One must think

32:24.290 --> 32:27.597
long and hard before
one casts it aside.

32:29.338 --> 32:31.993
Mm. Tommy's waiting.

32:32.037 --> 32:33.473
Oh, go, go. I...

32:33.516 --> 32:35.954
I hope you have
a nice dinner.

32:43.135 --> 32:47.487
Do you, uh,
think my pretty speech helped?

32:49.054 --> 32:50.969
More than you know.

32:52.100 --> 32:54.276
I need to make a phone call.

33:01.109 --> 33:04.286
Hey, baby.

33:04.330 --> 33:08.247
I'm gonna take Teacup upstairs.
It's nice and quiet up there.

33:08.290 --> 33:10.031
Yeah. She's had a stressful day.

33:10.075 --> 33:12.251
What you did today,

33:12.294 --> 33:14.949
that was the nicest thing
that anyone's ever done for me.

33:14.993 --> 33:16.733
Oh. No big deal.No. It absolutely was.

33:18.431 --> 33:19.606
Ow!
Oh...

33:19.649 --> 33:21.564
Son of a bitch.

33:21.608 --> 33:24.132
Please hide this.
Somewhere he can't find it.

33:24.176 --> 33:26.004
Okay. Thanks.

33:26.047 --> 33:27.440
Come on, Teacup.

33:27.483 --> 33:29.442
Oh, that's a good girl.

33:33.011 --> 33:34.969
It's a good day, huh?

33:35.013 --> 33:36.362
Is it?

33:36.405 --> 33:38.668
I mean, we got the dog back,
didn't we?

33:40.670 --> 33:44.457
All right. I know we might've
broken the law a little bit.

33:45.632 --> 33:47.982
You broke the law, a lot.

33:48.026 --> 33:49.636
And you made me an accomplice.

33:49.679 --> 33:52.508
All right, yeah, but you saw
how happy it made Jade, right?

33:52.552 --> 33:54.728
I think it was worth it.Absolutely,
you're right.

33:54.771 --> 33:57.600
The smile on Jade's face
more than makes up

33:57.644 --> 33:59.994
for the fact
that I could be disbarred.

34:00.038 --> 34:03.476
I'm sorry. I mean,
I had to do something.

34:03.519 --> 34:06.522
No, you didn't.
I had a plan.

34:06.566 --> 34:08.350
Yeah? So did I.

34:08.394 --> 34:09.656
Mine actually worked.

34:09.699 --> 34:11.266
That's not the point.

34:11.310 --> 34:13.181
Oh, no, no, no, no.
The point is that I finally do

34:13.225 --> 34:15.314
something right and you can't
even be happy about it.

34:15.357 --> 34:18.099
What am I supposed
to be happy about?

34:18.143 --> 34:20.014
For the last two years,
I've been pathetic Eli

34:20.058 --> 34:22.016
who-who can't finish
a screenplay,

34:22.060 --> 34:24.018
who can't help pay
the bills. I-I get it.

34:24.062 --> 34:26.020
You're frustrated with me.
Well, guess what?

34:26.064 --> 34:28.109
I'm frustrated with me, too.

34:28.153 --> 34:31.112
Eli, you're not pathetic.No?

34:31.156 --> 34:33.158
'Cause this morning, I couldn't
even defend my own home.

34:33.201 --> 34:34.768
My wife had to come save me.

34:34.811 --> 34:36.378
'Cause I thought he was gonna
beat you to a pulp.

34:36.422 --> 34:37.771
He probably
would have.

34:37.814 --> 34:39.338
But the fact
that you had to step in,

34:39.381 --> 34:41.209
that makes it hurt even worse.

34:43.168 --> 34:45.344
I was just trying to be helpful.I know.

34:45.387 --> 34:46.693
But sometimes, honey,

34:46.736 --> 34:48.695
I just need a fucking win.

34:48.738 --> 34:51.524
Okay? I just want
to feel like a man

34:51.567 --> 34:54.309
and save a dog
and have that be good enough.

34:57.182 --> 34:58.357
You're right.

34:59.575 --> 35:00.794
It was a good day.

35:00.837 --> 35:02.317
Thank you.

35:04.493 --> 35:06.713
I didn't lock the door.

35:06.756 --> 35:08.758
Okay, all right.
Call the police.

35:10.325 --> 35:11.631
Hey.

35:11.674 --> 35:13.198
Look, hey, man,
l-let me just start

35:13.241 --> 35:14.547
by offering my...

35:15.765 --> 35:17.245
TAYLOR:
No!

35:17.289 --> 35:20.553
Get off me, you bitch!

35:20.596 --> 35:23.730
Jade! Jade!

35:29.779 --> 35:31.564
Jade!

35:32.608 --> 35:35.350
Where the fuck is she?

35:56.197 --> 35:58.765
You broke my leg,
you crazy bitch!

35:58.808 --> 36:02.769
Fuck with my family again,
and I'll break the other one.

36:08.905 --> 36:11.386
How's your food?Excellent.

36:11.430 --> 36:13.780
Yours?Yeah, it's-it's really good.

36:13.823 --> 36:15.173
Good.

36:17.262 --> 36:19.612
So you're going
to college in the fall?

36:19.655 --> 36:22.136
Art school.Oh, that's right.

36:22.180 --> 36:24.138
You like to draw.

36:24.182 --> 36:25.705
That's cute.

36:26.749 --> 36:28.490
Yeah.

36:30.275 --> 36:32.190
Oh, what the hell?

36:32.233 --> 36:35.715
Sorry to interrupt your evening.
Hello, Tommy.

36:35.758 --> 36:37.369
Mrs. Grove.

36:37.412 --> 36:38.805
What are you
doing here, Mom?

36:38.848 --> 36:40.372
I need a moment.

36:40.415 --> 36:42.156
For what?

36:42.200 --> 36:43.766
I brought someone.

36:43.810 --> 36:46.682
Brad would like
to talk to you.

36:48.945 --> 36:50.686
I'm in the middle of dinner.

36:50.730 --> 36:53.820
Well, Tommy doesn't
mind. Do you?

36:53.863 --> 36:56.344
No.

37:02.307 --> 37:05.179
Simone...
Don't look at me.

37:05.223 --> 37:07.268
People will see.

37:07.312 --> 37:09.923
Okay.

37:09.966 --> 37:11.620
There's something
I want to say.

37:11.664 --> 37:14.188
Look, I only went out with
Amy to make you jealous.

37:14.232 --> 37:17.844
It was a, it was dumb thing to
do. I was just hurt, you know?

37:17.887 --> 37:20.499
Because I like you so much.

37:20.542 --> 37:24.242
But I was thinking that
if we put a name to what

37:24.285 --> 37:27.419
we've been doing, then I would
know how you felt about me,

37:27.462 --> 37:29.943
but you're not into it,
so I'll-- I will back off.

37:29.986 --> 37:31.684
You can look at me now.

37:41.259 --> 37:44.262
I must really like you a lot
to wear this god-awful thing.

37:49.789 --> 37:51.312
Well.

37:51.356 --> 37:53.749
I guess the wedding's
back on, then.

37:53.793 --> 37:56.752
Oh. Apparently so.

37:56.796 --> 37:59.451
Back to us.
Are you free Friday?

37:59.494 --> 38:01.453
Yes, ma'am.

38:01.496 --> 38:03.803
Don't call me ma'am.

38:03.846 --> 38:07.241
Yes, lover.

38:07.285 --> 38:09.939
Ma'am will be fine.

38:14.553 --> 38:16.946
Thank you again for inviting us.
Everything was lovely.

38:16.990 --> 38:18.992
VIVIAN:
We are so glad you came.

38:19.035 --> 38:21.473
I can't remember the last time
we laughed so hard.

38:21.516 --> 38:23.301
You're an absolute delight.

38:24.432 --> 38:26.695
I hope we see you again
very soon.

38:26.739 --> 38:28.915
Robert, you're a lucky man, son.

38:28.958 --> 38:31.352
Hope you know that.

38:32.397 --> 38:34.399
Yes, sir.

38:35.748 --> 38:37.750
Good night.
VIVIAN:
Good night.

38:55.333 --> 38:57.639
So how did you
figure it out?

39:05.038 --> 39:08.955
Oh, crap. I left a joint
in my pocket, didn't I?

39:09.999 --> 39:11.392
You did.

39:11.436 --> 39:13.916
You absolutely did.

39:13.960 --> 39:16.441
I knew something was up.

39:16.484 --> 39:18.573
You've been acting
strangely for weeks.

39:21.620 --> 39:23.317
So why did you smoke it?

39:23.361 --> 39:26.015
To get back at me?

39:28.714 --> 39:30.977
Well...

39:31.020 --> 39:33.371
I don't blame you.

39:34.372 --> 39:36.374
I'm sorry.

39:40.726 --> 39:43.772
My walk on the wild side
is over.

39:43.816 --> 39:45.383
Won't happen again.

39:59.571 --> 40:01.877
I have one question.What's that?

40:01.921 --> 40:04.053
Why did you want
to try marijuana?

40:08.884 --> 40:11.452
I thought it would be fun
to break the rules.

40:12.540 --> 40:14.542
Does that sound stupid?

40:16.152 --> 40:18.024
Not at all.

40:18.067 --> 40:23.029
My life feels like one of those
stupid swan napkins.

40:23.072 --> 40:26.859
It's rigid, it's all tight folds
and sharp edges.

40:26.902 --> 40:30.384
And people admire it,
but it takes

40:30.428 --> 40:33.387
so much work.

40:33.431 --> 40:37.391
And it's goddamned exhausting.

40:37.435 --> 40:38.914
Course it is.

40:40.916 --> 40:44.093
We've forgotten to find time
in our life for joy.

40:44.137 --> 40:45.878
Joy?

40:45.921 --> 40:48.489
Hell, I'd settle
for a few laughs now and then.

40:48.533 --> 40:52.493
I would love to hear you
laugh again.

40:52.537 --> 40:55.453
I'd break every rule
in the book for that.

40:57.585 --> 40:58.978
I'm starting to realize

40:59.021 --> 41:00.980
you're not the good little girl
I thought you were.

41:02.938 --> 41:04.157
No, sir.

41:04.200 --> 41:06.202
I'm a rebel.

41:07.595 --> 41:11.120
Okay. Okay.

41:12.600 --> 41:16.082
We've got to do
something, tonight.

41:16.125 --> 41:19.477
Something... crazy!

41:20.695 --> 41:22.784
Crazy and hilarious.

41:22.828 --> 41:25.004
But what? I mean...
what can we do? What?

41:25.047 --> 41:28.529
: I'm actually
getting excited.

41:35.580 --> 41:37.582
Rob...

41:43.501 --> 41:45.067
We're being too loud.

41:45.111 --> 41:47.200
I thought
you were a rebel.

41:47.243 --> 41:49.115
You're right.

41:55.034 --> 41:57.689
CORONER: If you visit your local morgue,

41:57.732 --> 42:00.518
you'll find the bodies
of good people

42:00.561 --> 42:02.998
who made bad choices.

42:06.785 --> 42:11.485
Some engaged
in reckless love affairs.

42:11.529 --> 42:16.490
Some invited violent strangers
into their home.

42:16.534 --> 42:18.753
And some kept dark secrets

42:18.797 --> 42:22.627
from those they loved.

42:22.670 --> 42:25.064
Yes, it's choices like these

42:25.107 --> 42:28.502
that lead to death.

42:28.546 --> 42:32.550
And more importantly, murder.

